<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="933" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d933">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001 /4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Taft</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">King of Siam</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-25"><hi rend="italic">October 25,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg to offer to Your Majesty the expression of the deep sympathy of the
                            Government and people of the United States in the loss sustained by Siam
                            in the death of His Late Majesty King Chulalongkorn, and my good wishes
                            for the prosperity and happiness of the Siamese people under your
                            reign.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>